%N A052548 a(n) = 2^n + 2.
%C A052548 The most "compact" sequence that satisfies Bertrand's Postulate. Begin with a(1) = 3 = n, then 2n - 2 = 4 = n_1, 2n_1 - 2 = 6 = n_2, 2n_2 - 2 = 10, etc. = a(n), hence there is guaranteed to be at least one prime between successive members of the sequence. - _Andrew S. Plewe_, Dec 11 2007
%C A052548 Number of 2-sided prudent polygons of area n, for n>0, see Beaton, p. 5. - _Jonathan Vos Post_, Nov 30 2010
